37 RIOT LAW CHANGES
38 SECTION 7.(a) G.S. 15A-534.8(b) reads as rewritten:
39 "(b) A defendant may be retained in custody not more than 24 48 hours from the time of
40 arrest without a determination being made under this section by a judge. If a judge has not acted
41 pursuant to this section within 24 48 hours of arrest, the magistrate shall act under the provisions
42 of this section."
43 SECTION 7.(b) Nothing in this section shall be construed as intended to prevent or
44 prohibit an individual's right to his or her exercise of free speech or the right to peaceable
45 assembly.
46 SECTION 7.(c) This section becomes effective December 1, 2026, and applies to
47 offenses committed on or after that date.
