19 MODIFY TAKING INDECENT LIBERTIES WITH CHILDREN OFFENSE
20 SECTION 13.(a) G.S. 14-202.1 reads as rewritten:
21 "§ 14-202.1. Taking indecent liberties with children.
22 (a) A person is guilty of taking indecent liberties with children if, being 16 years of age
23 or more and at least five years older than the child in question, he either:
24 (1) Willfully takes or attempts to take any immoral, improper, or indecent liberties with
25 any child of either sex under the age of 16 years for the purpose of arousing or gratifying sexual
26 desire; orin the first degree if the person is 16 years of age or more and at least five years older
27 than the child in question and willfully commits or attempts to commit any lewd or lascivious act
28 upon or with the body or any part or member of the body of any child of either sex less than 13
29 years of age. Violation of this subsection is a Class C felony.
30 (2) Willfully commits or attempts to commit any lewd or lascivious act upon or with the
31 body or any part or member of the body of any child of either sex under the age of 16 years.
32 (b) Taking indecent liberties with children is punishable as a Class F felony.A person is
33 guilty of taking indecent liberties with children in the second degree if the person is 16 years of
34 age or more and at least five years older than the child in question and willfully commits or
35 attempts to commit any lewd or lascivious act upon or with the body or any part or member of
36 the body of any child of either sex less than 16 years of age but at least 13 years of age. Violation
37 of this subsection is a Class D felony.
38 (c) A person is guilty of taking indecent liberties with children in the third degree if the
39 person is 16 years of age or more and at least five years older than the child in question and
40 willfully takes or attempts to take any immoral, improper, or indecent liberties with any child of
41 either sex less than 13 years of age for the purpose of arousing or gratifying sexual desire.
42 Violation of this subsection is a Class E felony.
43 (d) A person is guilty of taking indecent liberties with children in the fourth degree if the
44 person is 16 years of age or more and at least five years older than the child in question and
45 willfully takes or attempts to take any immoral, improper, or indecent liberties with any child of
46 either sex less than 16 years of age, but at least 13 years of age, for the purpose of arousing or
47 gratifying sexual desire. Violation of this subsection is a Class F felony.
48 (e) A person is guilty as a repeat offender of taking indecent liberties with a child if the
49 person is 18 years of age or older, commits any of the offenses in this section, and was previously
50 convicted of an offense requiring the person to register as a sex offender pursuant to Article 27A
51 of this Chapter. Violation of this subsection is a Class B1 felony."
